name: Ossiam Bloomberg Eurozone PAB NR UCITS ETF 1C (EUR)
description_en: The Ossiam Bloomberg Eurozone PAB NR UCITS ETF 1C (EUR) seeks to track the Bloomberg PAB Eurozone DM Large & Mid Cap index. The Bloomberg PAB Eurozone DM Large & Mid Cap index tracks large- and mid-cap securities from Eurozone countries. The index aims to reduce greenhouse gas intensity by at least 50 percent compared to the investment universe (Bloomberg Eurozone DM Large & Mid Cap index) and by an average of at least 7 per cent per year. The ETF's TER (total expense ratio) amounts to 0.17% p.a.. The Ossiam Bloomberg Eurozone PAB NR UCITS ETF 1C (EUR) is the only ETF that tracks the Bloomberg PAB Eurozone DM Large & Mid Cap index. The ETF replicates the performance of the underlying index by full replication (buying all the index constituents). The dividends in the ETF are accumulated and reinvested in the ETF. The Ossiam Bloomberg Eurozone PAB NR UCITS ETF 1C (EUR) has 293m Euro assets under management. The ETF was launched on 31 August 2018 and is domiciled in Luxembourg. Show more Show less

description_en: The Amundi MSCI Robotics & AI UCITS ETF Acc seeks to track the MSCI ACWI IMI Robotics & AI Filtered index. The MSCI ACWI IMI Robotics & AI Filtered index tracks companies from developed and emerging markets worldwide which are either involved in the development of artificial intelligence and robotics, or likely to profit from these developments. The stocks included are filtered according to ESG criteria (environmental, social and corporate governance). The parent index is the MSCI ACWI IMI. The ETF's TER (total expense ratio) amounts to 0.40% p.a.. The Amundi MSCI Robotics & AI UCITS ETF Acc is the only ETF that tracks the MSCI ACWI IMI Robotics & AI Filtered index. The ETF replicates the performance of the underlying index by full replication (buying all the index constituents). The dividends in the ETF are accumulated and reinvested in the ETF. name: Amundi MSCI Europe SRI Climate Paris Aligned UCITS ETF DR (C)
description_en: The Amundi MSCI Europe SRI Climate Paris Aligned UCITS ETF DR (C) seeks to track the MSCI Europe SRI Filtered PAB index. The MSCI Europe SRI Filtered PAB index tracks the European equity market performance considering only companies with high Environmental, Social and Governance (ESG) ratings relative to their sector peers, to ensure the inclusion of the best of class companies from an ESG perspective. Companies that generate significant portions of their revenues in non-sustainable activities are excluded. In addition, EU directives on climate protection are taken into account. The ETF's TER (total expense ratio) amounts to 0.18% p.a.. The Amundi MSCI Europe SRI Climate Paris Aligned UCITS ETF DR (C) is the cheapest and largest ETF that tracks the MSCI Europe SRI Filtered PAB index. The ETF replicates the performance of the underlying index by full replication (buying all the index constituents). The dividends in the ETF are accumulated and reinvested in the ETF. The Amundi MSCI Europe SRI Climate Paris Aligned UCITS ETF DR (C) is a very large ETF with 1,306m Euro assets under management.
